  "body": "**User Story**\r\n\r\nAs a user, I would like to send a message to someone without sharing my personal info. \r\nTo share my info, I would select 'Add to contact' option.\r\n\r\n**Description**\r\n\r\nWhen a user scans QR code of a contact, he is left with several options, such is: \r\n'Add to contacts', 'Send message', 'Send transaction', 'Share profile link' \r\nWhen you select an option of sending message without adding them to your contacts, you share your info regardless, as a contact request upon sending that message.\r\nSo, the person is in your contacts automatically. \r\n\r\nIn my opinion, it's not obvious that a user will share his/her details when sending a 1-1 message to a contact.\r\n\r\nThe question is, shouldn't we keep user anonymous when he is simply sending a message, without selecting 'add to contacts'? \r\n\r\n**Expected behavior**\r\n\r\nUser should have the ability to send a message without revealing their contact info\r\n\r\n**Actual behavior**\r\n\r\nAs soon as user clicks 'Send message', their contact data is revealed to that person without user's knowledge (a contact request is sent)\r\n\r\n**Reproduction**\r\n\r\n1. Scan QR code\r\n2. Select 'send message'\r\n**Actual result:** At this point a contact request is sent without the user's knowledge (for me it would not be obvious that I'm automatically adding that person to my contact list just by sending them a message)\r\n3. Send a message\r\n**Actual result:** At this point the reciever can see my name and contact data, since a contact request was sent.",
